1 HOUSE BILL NO. 700
2 INTRODUCED BY B. MERCER
3
4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT CHANGING THE AMORTIZATION PERIOD FOR THE
5 STATEWIDE DEFINED BENEFIT PUBLIC EMPLOYEE RETIREMENT SYSTEMS FROM 30 YEARS TO 25
6 YEARS; AMENDING SECTIONS 19-2-409, 19-3-109, 19-5-106, 19-6-107, 19-7-106, 19-8-106, 19-9-109, 19-
7 13-111, 19-17-117, AND 19-20-111, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 19-2-409, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "19-2-409. Plans to be funded on actuarially sound basis -- definition. (1) As required by Article
13 VIII, section 15, of the Montana constitution, each system must be funded on an actuarially sound basis. For
14 the purposes of this section, "actuarially sound basis" means that contributions to each retirement plan must be
15 sufficient to pay the full actuarial cost of the plan.
16 (2) (a) For a defined benefit plan, the full actuarial cost includes both the normal cost of providing
17 benefits as they accrue in the future and the cost of amortizing unfunded liabilities over a scheduled period of
18 no more than 30 years 25 years, except that with respect to the judges' retirement system, the highway patrol
19 officers' retirement system, the sheriffs' retirement system, and the game wardens' and peace officers'
20 retirement system, the unfunded liabilities must be paid over the periods provided for in 19-5-404, 19-6-404, 19-
21 7-404, and 19-8-504, respectively.
22 (b) For the defined contribution plan, the full actuarial cost is the contribution defined by law that is
23 payable to an account on behalf of the member."
24
25 Section 2. Section 19-3-109, MCA, is amended to read:
26 "19-3-109. Public employees' retirement system benefit policy statement. It is the policy of the
27 state that additional benefits may not be added to the public employees' retirement system unless the system
28 amortizes in 30 years 25 years or less and the additional benefit is projected to be fully funded in perpetuity."
